{"orig":"/Users/kalaverin/src/lang/nim/lib/pure/cstrutils.nim","nimble":"stdlib","moduleDescription":"This module supports helper routines for working with <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cstring</span></span></tt> without having to convert <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cstring</span></span></tt> to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">string</span></span></tt>, in order to save allocations.\n<h1><a class=\"toc-backref\" id=\"see-also\" href=\"#see-also\">See also</a></h1><ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"strutils.html\">strutils module</a> for working with <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">string</span></span></tt></li>\n</ul>\n","entries":[{"name":"startsWith","type":"skProc","line":27,"col":0,"code":"func startsWith(s, prefix: cstring): bool {.gcsafe, extern: \"csuStartsWith\",\n    raises: [], tags: [], forbids: [].}","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"s","type":"cstring"},{"name":"prefix","type":"cstring"}],"pragmas":["gcsafe","extern: \"csuStartsWith\"","raises: []","tags: []","forbids: []"]},"description":"<p>Returns true if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">s</span></span></tt> starts with <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">prefix</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>The JS backend uses the native <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">String</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">prototype</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">startsWith</span></span></tt> function.</p>\n"},{"name":"endsWith","type":"skProc","line":50,"col":0,"code":"func endsWith(s, suffix: cstring): bool {.gcsafe, extern: \"csuEndsWith\",\n    raises: [], tags: [], forbids: [].}","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"s","type":"cstring"},{"name":"suffix","type":"cstring"}],"pragmas":["gcsafe","extern: \"csuEndsWith\"","raises: []","tags: []","forbids: []"]},"description":"<p>Returns true if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">s</span></span></tt> ends with <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">suffix</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>The JS backend uses the native <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">String</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">prototype</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">endsWith</span></span></tt> function.</p>\n"},{"name":"cmpIgnoreStyle","type":"skProc","line":75,"col":0,"code":"func cmpIgnoreStyle(a, b: cstring): int {.gcsafe, extern: \"csuCmpIgnoreStyle\",\n    raises: [], tags: [], forbids: [].}","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"cstring"},{"name":"b","type":"cstring"}],"pragmas":["gcsafe","extern: \"csuCmpIgnoreStyle\"","raises: []","tags: []","forbids: []"]},"description":"Semantically the same as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">cmp</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">normalize</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Operator\">$</span><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">normalize</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Operator\">$</span><span class=\"Identifier\">b</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt>. It is just optimized to not allocate temporary strings. This should NOT be used to compare Nim identifier names, use <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">macros</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">eqIdent</span></span></tt> for that. Returns:<ul class=\"simple\"><li>0 if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">==</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">b</span></span></tt></li>\n<li>&lt; 0 if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">b</span></span></tt></li>\n<li>&gt; 0 if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">b</span></span></tt></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"cmpIgnoreCase","type":"skProc","line":104,"col":0,"code":"func cmpIgnoreCase(a, b: cstring): int {.gcsafe, extern: \"csuCmpIgnoreCase\",\n    raises: [], tags: [], forbids: [].}","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"cstring"},{"name":"b","type":"cstring"}],"pragmas":["gcsafe","extern: \"csuCmpIgnoreCase\"","raises: []","tags: []","forbids: []"]},"description":"Compares two strings in a case insensitive manner. Returns:<ul class=\"simple\"><li>0 if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">==</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">b</span></span></tt></li>\n<li>&lt; 0 if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">b</span></span></tt></li>\n<li>&gt; 0 if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">b</span></span></tt></li>\n</ul>\n"}]}